The Vice President of the United States met with Macedonian Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski to discuss the political and economic relationship between the two countries. They emphasized the importance of rule of law, freedom of independent media, and good inter-ethnic relations in Macedonia. The Vice President thanked Macedonia for its contributions to the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan. He also expressed hope for the resolution of the longstanding "name issue" between Macedonia and Greece, which would allow Macedonia to pursue NATO membership and fulfill its Euro-Atlantic aspirations.